    <p class="maintxt1">Cambodia</p>
    <p class="headtxt1">Brief About Cambodia:</p>
    <p class="plaintxt">
   Cambodia is one of the east Asian country, its capital is Phnom Penh City. Its official language is Khmer; its government is democracy. 
   Land area is 181.035 Sq. Kms and population 14,805,000 2009 estimate. 
   Density : 81.8 /sq.km, GDP : Us$./ 28.461 billion (per capita : Us.$ 2,100) .
     </p>
       
    <p class="headtxt1">Business Opportunities in Cambodia:</p>
    <p class="plaintxt">
    AAA feels Cambodia can be gold mine for any kind of export oriented agro project due to the following advantages :
    <ul class="plaintxt">
  
  <li>Large size of land (up to 10,000 hectares) is possible as government incentive in the form of economic land concession for captive production of raw material.</li> 
   <li>Attractive tax incentives are possible.</li> 
   <li>Exports from these countries enjoy concession duty imports in ASEAN, EU and USA.</li> 
   <li>As per the bilateral treaty between Vietnam and Cambodia many agro products  attract 0% import duty in Vietnam and the Vietnam has industrially grown and running short of raw material.</li>
   <li>Soil is  Fertile and huge water resources for irrigation and water transportation</li>

</ul>
</p>


   
    <p class="headtxt1">FDI Policy in Cambodia:</p>
    <p class="plaintxt">
   Cambodia welcomes foreign investment in all sectors, there is no discrimination between local investment and foreign investment. 
   The Cambodia also offers the following kind of attractive incentives for the investment projects : 
    <ul class="plaintxt">
  
   <li>Large size of land for agro projects as economic land concession.</li> 
   <li>0%  import duty for capital goods.</li> 
   <li>Tax holiday / confessional tax on the corporate tax.</li>
</ul>
</p>

       
